            <tr>
                  <td colspan="2" valign="top"><p style="font-size:15px; line-height:20px; color:#000; display:block;">Every candidate eligible (eligibility includes being in good academic standing, and passing the pre-placement test) for placements or internships leading to final placements has every likelihood to be placed well—and in many cases, land multiple opportunities. We assure placement opportunities to all eligible candidates.<br><br>

A long list of channels, portals, corporations, PR / advertising agencies and production houses have been associated with ITMI through placements and internships. <br><br>

The institute provides placement assistance to every eligible student towards gainful employment in the media and communication industries as well as in the burgeoning corporate world of CSR, through an elaborate, systematic process:<br><br>

-As a professional institute, our focus is on placements. Building students’ employability skills is paramount at ITMI.<br>
-A Placement Committee, headed by our Dean, scouts for opportunities and matches them with a student’s skills and aspirations. <br>
- Each programme entails an internship in the India Today Group. Our students are seriously considered for employment by the Group; however, job offers are based on requirements and competency. The Group and ITMI have a first-right-of-refusal arrangement. <br><br>

The way we groom each student ensures employability at various levels (not all students have the same level of skills). Starting from developing “employment communication skills” that include self-evaluation and résumé-writing, the process then includes building a portfolio, including live industry projects and demonstration of acquired skills. Skill development forms a major theme at ITMI, and we encourage students to demonstrate these on various platforms. Interface with the industry, governments, and the who’s-who of various walks of communication and other fields is also an important step; exposure to world thinking on various subjects helps students gain one of the most important goals at ITMI—developing a worldview. <br><br>

A formal process is adopted for obtaining internships and placements, whereby each individual student’s work is showcased to the industries. Internships are expected to lead to job offers, and in case they don’t, students may be given other options through institutional collaborations with the industry.  <br><br>

Our graduates command a high degree of respect in the industry, and many of our alumni are well known in the industry. Some of the biggest names in media and communication have been associated with ITMI. <br>

<h3 style="margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Professional associations</strong></h3><br>
Building a worldview is critical to employability. That is why, in addition to belonging to one of the largest media groups in India, ITMI has recently been proactive in associating itself internationally: U.S., Canada, Austria, Israel and Sweden are a few countries whose agencies encourage their own media (and related) guests to visit ITMI campus and share their professional expertise with our students. In the industry, too, a growing number of companies and media houses have associated with us through internships and placements.<br><br>
This kind of association has resulted in a quantum leap in our students’ understanding of world media and global standards. Workshops by Israeli film scriptwriters and by Swedish journalists, interactions with top American and Canadian journalists, lawmakers and policymakers, with ambassadors and communication experts are a norm at ITMI.
</p></td>
